<TEXT>
here are some facts and figures on romania 
 
the land romania covers 91699 square miles about the size of 
oregon it is in southeastern europe bordered by hungary 
yugoslavia bulgaria the black sea and the soviet union principal 
rivers are the danube and its tributary the prut the country is 
cut by the carpathian mountains 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the people romanias population is estimated at 23 million 
bucharest the capital is by far the largest city with a 
population of about 19 million most of the people are romanian 
but about 10 percent are of hungarian or german extraction the 
dominant religion is the romanian orthodox church 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the economy romania is a large exporter of petroleum and 
natural gas and has iron coal and copper mines as well chief 
agricultural products include corn wheat wine grapes sugar beets 
and potatoes 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
history the country obtained full independence from the turks 
in 1878 and was proclaimed a kingdom in 1881 
romania was one of the victorious allies in world war i but 
after the war it was wracked by political violence in 1940 ion 
antonescu overthrew king carol ii and established a dictatorship 
that was aligned with germany in world war ii as the german axis 
foundered king michael was able to reestablish a monarchy in 
1944 but occupying soviet troops led to the proclamation of a 
communist republic in 1947 
nicolae ceausescu 71 took power in 1965 after the death of his 
mentor gheorghe gheorghiudej his 24 years of hardline rule 
ended with his ouster friday 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

